      <h1>Understanding the Effects of Plastic Pollution</h1>

      <h2>What is Plastic Pollution?</h2>
      <p>Plastic pollution occurs when plastic waste accumulates in the environment. It’s especially harmful in oceans, rivers, and coastlines where it threatens wildlife, contaminates food chains, and disrupts entire ecosystems.</p>

      <div class="image-block">
        <img src="https://imgs.search.brave.com/1R6RPSe1iyw6nBJlzmdWd_oBVKWFl9224yVlKdrlowA/rs:fit:860:0:0:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9tZWRp/YS5nZXR0eWltYWdl/cy5jb20vaWQvMTQ2/NTE0MzAyL3Bob3Rv/L3doYXQtd2FzdGUu/anBnP3M9NjEyeDYx/MiZ3PTAmaz0yMCZj/PVpVUzhfaTVNenFj/My12cDhCRVZXZU9W/Q25xNWtWQkRYMzlZ/cXRibTJyRXM9" alt="Plastic waste in ocean">
        <div class="caption">Plastic debris pollutes beaches and waterways globally.</div>
      </div>

      <h2>Key Facts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Over 8 million tons of plastic end up in the ocean each year.</li>
        <li>There are over 5 trillion plastic particles floating in our seas.</li>
        <li>Plastic can take up to 500 years to decompose.</li>
        <li>Every minute, the equivalent of one garbage truck of plastic is dumped into the ocean.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Main Causes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Single-use plastics like bags, straws, and packaging</li>
        <li>Poor recycling and waste disposal systems</li>
        <li>Global overproduction of plastic materials</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="image-block">
        <img src="https://imgs.search.brave.com/nsafozodwh19i_WL2D5L201Ov0t68wrY2L0zAn3iz6w/rs:fit:860:0:0:0/g:ce/aHR0cHM6Ly9uYXR1/cmVjb2RlLm9yZy93/cC1jb250ZW50L3Vw/bG9hZHMvMjAxOS8w/Ni9SZXVzYWJsZS1J/dGVtcy0xMDI0eDY4/My5qcGc" alt="Plastic reuse">
        <div class="caption">Switching to reusable items is a powerful solution.</div>
      </div>

      <h2>Environmental & Health Effects</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Marine life consumes plastic, mistaking it for food.</li>
        <li>Microplastics are found in drinking water and seafood.</li>
        <li>Toxic chemicals from plastics harm animal and human health.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What You Can Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Reduce use of plastic products—especially single-use ones.</li>
        <li>Participate in local clean-up events.</li>
        <li>Support laws that restrict plastic waste and encourage recycling.</li>
        <li>Educate your community about the issue.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="image-block">
        <img src="https://www.reuters.com/resizer/v2/Z5I6XFFI55K2FKMXSN7SXIIRCY.jpg?auth=2760d5daa44da83c9822b2569928e08bc76f8057950be1abb33c5feaa410a1ca&width=960&quality=80" alt="People cleaning beach">
        <div class="caption">Community efforts make a huge difference in local environments.</div>
      </div>

